<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CityWeather API Documentation</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/css/bootstrap.min.css">
</head>
<body>
    <main class="container mt-5">
        <section class="text-center">
            <h1>Welcome to CityWeather API</h1>
            <p class="lead">This API allows you to retrieve real-time weather information for cities around the world.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-4">
            <h2>Available Endpoints</h2>
            <ul class="list-group">
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    <strong>GET /api/weather</strong>
                    <p>Retrieve weather information for a specified city.</p>
                    <p><strong>Query Parameter:</strong> <code>city</code> - The name of the city (default is Tel Aviv).</p>
                    <p><strong>Example:</strong> <code>GET /api/weather?city=London</code></p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-4">
            <h2>Sample Response</h2>
            <pre class="bg-light p-3">
{
    "Temperature_c": 25.6,
    "Temperature_f": 78.1,
    "WindSpeed_kph": 10.5,
    "Country": "Israel",
    "City": "Tel Aviv",
}
            </pre>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-4">
            <h2>Getting Started</h2>
            <p>To get started with the API, simply send a GET request to the endpoint with the desired city as a query parameter.</p>
            <p>If no city is specified, the API will return weather information for Tel Aviv by default.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-4">
            <h2>Contact</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions or encounter issues, please contact the API support team.</p>
        </section>
    </main>
</body>
</html>
